cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with a combinatorial optimization problem (matching) in a probabilistic setting, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The use of algorithms and approximation ratios suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the focus on achieving a better approximation ratio than previous work suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
